<h2>Chapter 7: Entity SEO and AI Overviews &#123;#chapter-7&#125;</h2>
<p>AI Overviews changed how Google uses entity data. The old system matched queries to pages. The new system matches queries to entities, then finds the best sources for those entities.</p>
<p>This is why entity SEO matters more in 2026 than it did in 2024. AI search engines do not scan blog posts word by word. They pull from entity graphs.</p>
<h3>How AI Overviews Use Entities</h3>
<p>When an AI Overview generates an answer, it:</p>
<ol>
<li>Parses the query into constituent entities</li>
<li>Retrieves entity data from the Knowledge Graph</li>
<li>Identifies authoritative sources for those entities</li>
<li>Synthesizes an answer with citations</li>
</ol>
<p>If your site is recognized as authoritative for a given entity, you get cited. If not, a competitor does.</p>
<p>According to research, only 25% of frequently mentioned brands appear as primary sources in AI-generated answers. That means 75% of brands are not recognized as entities worth citing. Even when they rank well in traditional search.</p>
<h3>Optimizing for AI Search Visibility</h3>
<p><a href="/blog/what-is-geo/">Generative engine optimization (GEO)</a> and entity SEO overlap heavily. The tactics that build entity authority also improve AI search citations.</p>
<p>Key actions for <a href="/blog/ai-overview-optimization/">AI Overview optimization</a>:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Add <a href="/blog/structured-data-ai-search/">structured data that AI search engines read</a>.</strong> Schema markup is how AI systems verify entity claims.</li>
<li><strong>Build citability.</strong> Write clear, factual statements that AI can extract as answers. Our <a href="/blog/ai-citability-score/">AI citability score guide</a> explains the scoring factors.</li>
<li><strong>Get cited by authoritative sources.</strong> When other trusted entities mention your entity, AI systems increase your authority score. See our guide on <a href="/blog/get-cited-ai-search/">getting cited by AI search engines</a>.</li>
<li><strong>Optimize for the <a href="/blog/answer-economy-strategy/">answer economy</a>.</strong> Structure content so AI can pull direct answers with attribution.</li>
</ul>
